# Link Ingest Discord Surface

## Outcome

Add the first explicit Discord surface for joelclaw link ingest without turning random Discord links into automatic captures.

## Decision

`pi-discord-threads` stays the operator surface. It detects explicit ingest/capture commands, creates or reuses a Discord thread, sends a `link/ingest.requested` event to Central Inngest, and records the Discord mention to source mapping in the local registry.

Bare or lightly annotated URLs stay in-phase as ordinary Pi thread input. Explicit commands are out-of-phase source capture requests: `/pi ingest`, `!pi ingest`, and `/pi capture`. The `/pi capture url:<url> note:<optional>` alias is operator-facing wording only; it reuses the ingest payload and does not inherit active workstream context unless the note says so.

It does not download media, transcribe audio, scrape articles, scrape X, summarize, or write `.brain` capture pages. Those are worker responsibilities.

## Implementation receipt

Added:

- `/pi ingest url:<url> note:<optional>`
- `/pi capture url:<url> note:<optional>`
- `!pi ingest <url> [note]`
- `linkIngest` config:
  - `enabled`
  - `inngestUrl`
  - `eventKeyEnv`
  - `eventKeySecretName`
  - `signingKeyEnv`
  - `signingKeySecretName`
  - `statusBridgeEnabled`
  - `defaultVisibility`
  - `defaultSite`
  - `wzrrdCandidate`
  - `requestTimeoutMs`
- `src/link-ingest.ts` for URL extraction, URL normalization, `sourceId`, `mentionId`, event payload construction, and Event API POST.
- `src/link-ingest-status-bridge.ts` for Inngest Connect status events back to Discord threads.
- `Registry.linkIngests` for local Discord mention to source mapping.
- `Registry.linkIngests[*].statusUpdates` for idempotent posted status receipts.

The emitted event shape is:

```text
link/ingest.requested
v=2026-06-17.1
id=link-ingest:discord:<guildId>:<channelId>:<messageOrInteractionId>
sourceId=sha256(normalizedUrl)
mentionId=discord:<guildId>:<channelId>:<messageOrInteractionId>
```

## Verification

Passed locally:

```sh
npm run typecheck
npm run build
npm run brain:check
npx tsx -e "<prepareLinkIngest smoke>"
node dist/index.js doctor --config ~/.config/pi-discord-threads/config.json
node dist/index.js install-launch-agent --config ~/.config/pi-discord-threads/config.json --restart
```

Smoke output confirmed:

- event name: `link/ingest.requested`
- schema version: `2026-06-17.1`
- source ID length: `64`
- mention ID: `discord:g:c:m`
- normalized URL: `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=abc123`
- extracted context: `this is interesting`
- Central Inngest API reachable on `127.0.0.1:8288`.
- Local `secrets` now has `inngest_event_key`, copied from `/Users/Shared/joelclaw/etc/inngest/inngest.env` without printing the value.
- LaunchAgent `com.joelhooks.pi-discord-threads` restarted and is running from `/Users/joel/Code/joelhooks/pi-discord-threads/dist/index.js`.

2026-06-17 status bridge receipt:

- Added `inngest@4.4.0`.
- Added `link/ingest.accepted` and `link/ingest.classified` Connect consumers inside the existing Discord bot process.
- Added `source/archive.completed`, `video/metadata.completed`, `article/extract.completed`, `source/transcript.completed`, `source/summary.completed`, `capture/item.ready`, and `capture/item.failed` Connect consumers inside the existing Discord bot process.
- Seeded local `inngest_signing_key` from Central Inngest env without printing the value.
- Verified isolated live-Inngest status bridge smoke with a fake Discord client and temp registry; it posted one fake status and persisted `statusUpdates`.
- Rebuilt and restarted LaunchAgent `com.joelhooks.pi-discord-threads`.
- `daemon.log` showed `link ingest status bridge connected to Central Inngest` and `Sent WORKER_READY`.
- `doctor` reported `statusBridge=enabled`, `eventKeySecret=inngest_event_key`, and `signingKeySecret=inngest_signing_key`.

Current status events handled:

```text
link/ingest.accepted
link/ingest.classified
source/archive.completed
video/metadata.completed
video/media.completed
video/audio-transcript.completed
article/extract.completed
x/snapshot.completed
source/transcript.completed
source/summary.completed
capture/item.ready
capture/index.completed
capture/item.failed
```

The bridge posts one Discord status per logical event/mention and records the Discord message ID in the local registry.

2026-06-17 failure bridge receipt:

- Added `capture/item.failed` status handling.
- Failure embeds show `failed step`, `reason`, optional error details, Brain path, and manifest path.
- The local registry already supported `failed`, so no registry shape change was needed.
- The Central live smoke used a synthetic non-Discord mention, so it verified event delivery and Brain state but did not post into a real Discord thread.

2026-06-17 transcript bridge receipt:

- Added `source/transcript.completed` status handling.
- Transcript embeds show `transcriptStatus`, text path, VTT path when available, metadata path, word count, and degraded reason/error when captions are unavailable.
- Extended the local registry status union with `transcript_processed` so posted transcript receipts survive restarts.

2026-06-17 capture alias receipt:

- Added `/pi capture url:<url> note:<optional>` as a slash-command alias for the existing link ingest event path.
- Reused `sendLinkIngest`/`prepareLinkIngest`; no new capture pipeline or event name.
- Kept `!pi ingest <url> [note]` as the only prefix fallback ingest command so bare URLs remain normal in-phase Pi input.
- Removed the raw `mentionId` field from accepted Discord embeds to avoid surfacing Discord internal IDs in operator status.
- Added `npm run smoke:capture` coverage for capture with and without a note, existing prefix ingest, and bare URL non-command routing.

Verification passed:

```sh
npm run smoke:capture
npm run typecheck
npm run build
npm run brain:check
git diff --check
```

